snippet.textDisplay: Poker pro here. One thing most non-pros don't get is how skill VS luck functions in the game. As blinds get higher and stacks get shorter, the game becomes almost 100% luck. This is why in major tournaments blinds only go up every few hours and you play for several days, to allow skill the time to play more of a role. Even then, luck is still important. In this game, the blinds went up too fast for Maria to do much. She even got really lucky early on and still couldn't win when the blinds increased. Give her a few days with no rush and she probably would've annihilated them.
